    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is a concours-level 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2), featuring the high-revving 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant paired with a precise Getrag G96 6-speed manual transaxle. This specimen boasts a documented LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a recent borescope inspection confirming zero cylinder bore scoring. The chassis retains its factory-spec rigidity, complemented by a pristine MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension setup. Finished in Arctic Silver over black leather, the exterior shows original paint depth with zero track-use fatigue. Mechanically flawless, the throttle response is instantaneous, and the four-piston monoblock Brembo calipers provide fade-free deceleration. An investment-grade example for the discerning collector.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
